WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.859 --> 00:00:06.760
&gt;&gt;commentator: Hi all. Welcome to Authors@Google
in New York. And we're here to welcome Amanda

00:00:06.760 --> 00:00:10.690
Pressner and Holly Corbett, two of the three
lost girls.

00:00:10.690 --> 00:00:14.929
We sent out information about it. They have
a website and now they have a book and it's

00:00:14.929 --> 00:00:20.800
soon to be made into an ABC show next fall,
I think it is by Jerry Bruckheimer. So we're

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:23.790
really happy to welcome them-them here.

00:00:23.790 --> 00:00:28.880
And also one other note, there's a third lost
girl, Jenn, but she is actually I think working

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:32.279
with the Food Network on a shoot so she couldn't
be here today. But, so there's three, but

00:00:32.279 --> 00:00:34.230
we're happy to have two of them.

00:00:34.230 --> 00:00:40.730
So the three of these wonderful women in 2006
basically paused their jobs as they described

00:00:40.730 --> 00:00:45.620
to me earlier and they wanted to travel the
world for a year. And so this book is just

00:00:45.620 --> 00:00:51.230
a memoir of them traveling the world and what
it was like to kind of let go of their life

00:00:51.230 --> 00:00:57.420
in New York and jobs, boyfriends, family,
and travel the world.

00:00:57.420 --> 00:01:00.140
So welcome to them. And then Lee is gonna,
they're gonna read a little bit from the-the

00:01:00.140 --> 00:01:02.700
memoir and then Lee's gonna moderate some
questions.

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:12.460
And feel free once we open it up to answer
questions at the mike. And please join me

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:19.040
in welcoming them to Google.

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:20.360
[applause]

00:01:20.360 --> 00:01:26.140
&gt;&gt;Lee: Well thank you guys for coming.

00:01:26.140 --> 00:01:35.270
&gt;&gt;Holly Corbett: Yeah, thanks for having us
here. We're really excited to be here at Google.

00:01:35.270 --> 00:01:55.509
We kind of wrote up some things to say, but
we're pretty much just gonna ad lib so --

00:01:55.509 --> 00:02:11.570
&gt;&gt;Lee: We can have people if you wanna kind
of come like in from the sides and the back

00:02:11.570 --> 00:02:20.000
row. I know you're gonna be on the computer
and that's kind of --

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:25.300
&gt;&gt;Amanda Pressner Come on in. Snuggle in.
[laughs]

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:28.000
&gt;&gt;Lee: people are working through their lunch
but --

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:33.379
&gt;&gt;Holly Corbett: Sounds great â€“ you guys
